function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(first(word)), words)
end
```
This function uses the `filter` function to iterate over the input list `words`. It keeps a word in the list if the first letter of the word is uppercase, which is checked using the `isuppercase` function. The `first` function is used to get the first letter of each word.
